{"word":"λαμπάς","slug":"λαμπάς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λαμπάς1</b></el> <el>(λαμπάς, άδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:λάμπω'><el>λάμπω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a torch</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <i>a beacon-light</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—later, <i>an oil-lamp</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of the sun, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἡ ἐπιοῦσα λ.</el> the coming <i>light</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> the next day, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the torch-race</i>, like <el>λαμπαδηδρομία</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>λαμπάδα δραμεῖν</el> to run <i>the race</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div> <hr/> <el><b>λαμπάς2</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:λαμπρός'><el>λαμπρός</el></a>\n<p/><i>gleaming with torches</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}